    "narrative": "The Austin Waves\u2019 offensive outlook for 2026-04-11 is headlined by the elite efficiency of **Kyle Tucker** (81.02) and **Jackson Merrill** (75.27). **Kyle Tucker** represents our safest high-floor play against Jack Leiter; with a strong xwOBA of 0.372 and beneficial wind conditions, he is the anchor of our lineup. Similarly, **Jackson Merrill** benefits from a porous matchup against Ryan Feltner and a high-utility stolen base environment\u2014Feltner\u2019s slow delivery provides the exact leverage we need to capitalize on the scarcity of the SB category. **Gunnar Henderson** (69.67) also warrants attention; despite the tough matchup against Logan Webb, his spot at the top of the order and park factors in his favor keep him as a primary engine for our Runs and RBI accumulation.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today's card was bypassing **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (50.63). While his raw talent is indisputable, his efficiency rating struggled against Joe Ryan\u2019s 3.32 xERA. In a 5x5 Roto format where efficiency is king, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** fell just below the threshold of our starting nine, as the optimizer favored the high-upside speed threats and superior platoon matchups presented by the likes of **Luis Robert Jr.** (63.03) and **Andy Pages** (63.51). **Andy Pages**, in particular, sees a notable boost from wind patterns favoring hitters, positioning him as a sneaky value play compared to the more household names currently riding the pine.\n\nManagement must remain vigilant regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" designations for **Gunnar Henderson**, **Jackson Merrill**, and **Andy Pages**. While our scoring model accounts for assumed spots, any drastic drop in batting order will erode the marginal gains currently propping up their scores. Additionally, while **Drake Baldwin** (50.12) and **Liam Hicks** (51.55) are active, their proximity to our \"marginal\" floor means we are effectively punting the catcher position to prioritize the volume and stolen base upside of our outfield and middle infield core. Proceed with caution on the late-afternoon updates.",
